title: 820-02443 5V 0.045A
message:
Tested on genuine 96W charger via USB C

Very small liquid damage on UR660 and UF800

PPBUS_AON - 12.25V
PP3V8_AON - 0.68V (0.144V in diode mode)

PP3V8_AON goes to UR660 which was affected by liquid so I removed UR660 but still got only 0.68V

All LDOs on all CD3217 are correct in diode mode.


Any idea?

title: 820-02443 5V 0.045A
message:
First be sure R5710/11 are both good.
Next check U5700 voltages from page 34 (left side).

title: 820-02443 5V 0.045A
message:
Found small liquid damage on R5710/11 which I missed.
U5700/8 pad was fried.

Restored damaged pad and replaced those two resistors and all works fine :)

Gain. Many thanks :)
